[?2004l[?2004hroot@6cf6b9c9e5b7:/app# panda --prompt 'You are provided with a JSON file located at '"'"'/app/users.json'"'"' containing user data. Your task is to use jq to transform this data and produce a new JSON file at '"'"'/app/active_users_report.json'"'"' that meets the following criteria:
[?2004l[?2004h> 1. **Filter Users**: Include only users who are '"'"'active'"'"' (status is '"'"'active'"'"').
[?2004l[?2004h> 2. **Parse and Format Dates**: Convert the '"'"'last_login'"'"' ISO 8601 timestamp into a date string in the format '"'"'YYYY-MM-DD'"'"'.
[?2004l[?2004h> 3. **Extract and Rename Fields**:
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Extract '"'"'id'"'"' as '"'"'user_id'"'"'.
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Extract '"'"'username'"'"'.
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Extract '"'"'email'"'"'.
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Extract and format '"'"'last_login'"'"'.
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Extract the count of roles as '"'"'role_count'"'"'.
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Extract the first role from the '"'"'roles'"'"' array as '"'"'primary_role'"'"' (if roles exist, otherwise null).
[?2004l[?2004h> 4. **Sort Users**: Sort the resulting users alphabetically by their '"'"'username'"'"' in ascending order.
[?2004l[?2004h> 5. **Output Format**: The output must be a JSON array of objects formatted with indentation of 2 spaces.
[?2004l[?2004h> 6. **Save Command**: Save the exact jq command you execute to a file named '"'"'/app/cmd.sh'"'"'. This file should contain the complete jq command used to generate the output, including all options and arguments.
[?2004l[?2004h> 7. **Save Arguments**: Save all jq arguments(excluding input/output files) to a YAML file named '"'"'/app/jq_args.yaml'"'"'. This file should contain exactly two keys:
