[?2004l[?2004h>    
[?2004l[?2004h>    '"'"'/app/jq_args.yaml'"'"' Example format:
[?2004l[?2004h>    ```
[?2004l[?2004h>    filter: "group_by(.address.city)"
[?2004l[?2004h>    args:
[?2004l[?2004h>      - "--unbuffered"
[?2004l[?2004h>      - "--argjson min_count 5"
[?2004l[?2004h>      - "--tab"
[?2004l[?2004h>    ```
[?2004l[?2004h>    
[?2004l[?2004h>    '"'"'/app/jq_args.yaml'"'"' will be used to construct and execute a single jq command as follows:
[?2004l[?2004h>    `jq $(yq -r '"'"'.args[]'"'"' /app/jq_args.yaml) "$(yq -r '"'"'.filter'"'"' /app/jq_args.yaml)" /app/users.json > /app/active_users_report.json`
[?2004l[?2004h>    
[?2004l[?2004h>    For the example above, the constructed command would be:
[?2004l[?2004h>    `jq --unbuffered --argjson min_count 5 --tab '"'"'group_by(.address.city)'"'"' /app/users.json > /app/active_users_report.json`
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h>    This means:
[?2004l[?2004h>    1. All arguments in the '"'"'args'"'"' list will be passed directly to jq
